{"id": "EUVD-2025-18139", "enisaUuid": "14055a9c-4177-303e-85ae-188f43a2d364", "description": "os.OpenFile(path, os.O_CREATE|O_EXCL) behaved differently on Unix and Windows systems when the target path was a dangling symlink. On Unix systems, OpenFile with O_CREATE and O_EXCL flags never follows symlinks. On Windows, when the target path was a symlink to a nonexistent location, OpenFile would create a file in that location. OpenFile now always returns an error when the O_CREATE and O_EXCL flags are both set and the target path is a symlink.", "datePublished": "2025-06-11T18:35:43", "dateUpdated": "2025-06-11T18:35:43", "baseScore": 5.5, "baseScoreVersion": "3.1", "baseScoreVector": "CVSS:3.1/AV:L/AC:L/PR:L/UI:N/S:U/C:N/I:H/A:N", "references": ["https://go.dev/cl/672396", "https://go.dev/issue/73702", "https://groups.google.com/g/golang-announce/c/ufZ8WpEsA3A", "https://pkg.go.dev/vuln/GO-2025-3750", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-0913"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-0913"], "assigner": "Go", "epss": 0.01, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "15517503-82c5-33e0-8822-4239f67c6b4a", "product": {"name": "syscall"}, "product_version": "1.24.0-0 <1.24.4"}, {"id": "499cea05-5401-371f-a5c4-6ebdba6aa24c", "product": {"name": "os"}, "product_version": "0 <1.23.10"}, {"id": "8d5e18fe-eab6-3de1-9235-1294427cec44", "product": {"name": "os"}, "product_version": "1.24.0-0 <1.24.4"}, {"id": "b0dd95ca-3035-3c88-a82a-3401a97f6d76", "product": {"name": "syscall"}, "product_version": "0 <1.23.10"}], "enisaIdVendor": [{"id": "315a6edd-c135-3c74-80eb-b92b2f897362", "vendor": {"name": "Go standard library"}}], "isExploited": false}